&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thinkific is a learning commerce platform that helps learning businesses turn knowledge into impact. By bringing together community, courses, and content with commerce, we power transformative learning experiences that help businesses grow their revenue—and reach millions of learners around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a team of 300+ Thinkers building products that matter. Every role at Thinkific contributes to raising the bar for online learning, supporting learning businesses, and creating real-world impact. You’ll work alongside curious, collaborative teammates who care deeply about what they build and who they build it for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to a fair, inclusive, and human hiring experience. Our team is here to guide you every step of the way, so you always know what to expect!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join us at Thinkific. As a Principal Engineer at Thinkific, you’ll act as a force multiplier, making our engineering team better by advocating for best practices and helping fellow engineers find ways to level up their skills. You will act as a bridge to match business and technical strategy and influence the longer term technical roadmaps of our systems and overall architecture. You’ll speak to the technical aspects of the product, connect planned work for multiple products to business strategy, and most importantly, influence others around you towards these goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s how you’ll accomplish this:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a strategic area within R&amp;amp;D from a technical perspective - your objective is to ensure business success and impact through technical decisions and implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own overall architecture, collaborate on prioritization of work, implementation details, technical stack decisions, and overall health of systems and features within your domains, ensuring alignment with higher level technical strategy and guiding principles as set out by the Lead Architect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with engineering leaders and the Lead Architect to develop the roadmap and break things down into smaller tasks for engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with senior, staff, and senior staff engineers who will own, develop, and maintain systems &amp;amp; features within the domains you oversee, ensuring they are following the direction and vision you have set.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Director of Engineering to stay updated on business strategy into the future and pair with them on ownership of the domains, the principal from the technical perspective and the director from the strategic &amp;amp; organizational perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for writing and reviewing technical documentation in your business and technical domain, and sponsor other engineers within your area to maintain, add, and update as well.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own SaaS metrics relating to your domains, like COGs, and be accountable for the overall costs, reliability, and scalability of your domains in relation to business value.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain visibility outside of the organization, regularly contributing to the engineering blog, giving talks at conferences, and overall influencing engineering culture inside &amp;amp; outside the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review technical proposals for other engineers and help them level up by mentoring them and helping them solve complex problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play an active role in our hiring process to help us continue to scale our Engineering team, from suggesting skills gaps, to interviewing candidates, to conducting assignment reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in on-call rotations as required, troubleshooting production issues to maintain service reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt
